Ion Chirinciuc was born in Ungheni, Moldova.
He moved to Romania to study at the Octav Băncilă Art School in Iași, and later relocated to Bucharest to pursue a career in music.

In November 2017, Vanotek released his debut album, No Sleep, distributed by Global Records.
The album spawned a string of singles, including "Tell Me Who" and "Back to Me" with Eneli, which attained success in countries such as Romania and Russia.
In October 2019 Vanotek released single "Take Me" in collaboration with Ukrainian singer Myata.
